Package com.intellij.openapi.vcs

Interface FilePath

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CvsFilePath, FilePathImpl, LocalFilePath, RemoteFilePath

    public interface FilePath
    Represents a path to a (possibly non-existing) file on disk or in a VCS repository.

      • getVirtualFile

        VirtualFile getVirtualFile()
        Returns:
        a virtual file that corresponds to this path, or null if the virtual file is no more valid.

      • getVirtualFileParent

        VirtualFile getVirtualFileParent()
        Returns:
        the virtual file that corresponds to the parent file path, or null if the virtual file is no more valid.

      • getIOFile

        java.io.File getIOFile()
        Returns:

        See Also:
        isNonLocal()

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Returns:
        the file name (without directory component)

      • getPresentableUrl

        java.lang.String getPresentableUrl()
        Returns:
        the path to the file in the format suitable for displaying in the UI, e.g. for local file it is the path to this file with system separators.

      • isDirectory

        boolean isDirectory()

      • isUnder

        boolean isUnder(FilePath parent,
                boolean strict)
        Check if the provided file is an ancestor of the current file.
        Parameters:
        parent - a possible parent
        strict - if false, the method also returns true if files are equal
        Returns:
        true if this file is ancestor of the parent.

      • getParentPath

        FilePath getParentPath()
        Returns:
        the parent path or null if there is no parent of this file.

      • isNonLocal

        boolean isNonLocal()
        Returns:
        true if the path does not represents a file in the local file system
